Add Phaser intellisense in VS Code

Phaser is open source JavaScript based game development framework for HTML-5 game development. VS code is also open source and commonly used IDE for web development. but there no Extension available for intellisense Phaser in Vs code.

This can be done in 3 steps .

    First Download the definition (https://github.com/photonstorm/phaser/blob/master/types/phaser.d.ts) from phaser’s git-hub page.
    Create a jsconfig.json file at (raiz do jogo) your root/ base directory like below

3. Create a folder named “defs” in you root/base directory and add that def file phaser.d.ts in this folder.

That's it now type some code, it should auto-complete the Phaser API
Bonus

you can add additional def files for matter, canvas, webgl in your def folder for additional benifits.

all defs can be downloaded from here (https://github.com/photonstorm/phaser/tree/master/types).

